Inputs:

Train detection.
This input detects if the train is approaching or passing through the rail crossing by having the train's wheels complete a circuit in the tracks. If the train is detected, Train detection is true.

Gate position   
 This input returns if the gate is open or closed. If the gate is closed, Gate position is true

Blockage detection 
This input detects if there is a blockage on the track. If there is a blockage, Blockage detection is true.


Outputs:

Gates 
Controls gates either side of the rails. To close, set gates to true.

Stop the train. 
If true this output stops the train to prevent collision.  

